 {"id": "bd-nsn-1", "title": "PORT: ns_name sub-bead 1 \u2014 core::resolv::dns_name module", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-nsn-epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T09:42:59.817017Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T09:42:59.817017Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T09:42:59.817017Z", "resolution": "Added crates/frankenlibc-core/src/resolv/dns_name.rs with: NS_MAXLABEL=63, NS_MAXCDNAME=255, NS_MAXDNAME=1025 constants; pub enum NameError (OutputTooSmall, InvalidLabel, EmptyLabelInMiddle, InvalidEscape, CompressionPointer); pub fn name_ntop(wire: &[u8], dst: &mut [u8]) -> Result<usize, NameError> per RFC 1035 \u00a73.1; pub fn name_pton(text: &[u8], dst: &mut [u8]) -> Result<usize, NameError>. Both preserve abi byte-for-byte semantics (high-bits-set length byte rejected as CompressionPointer; \\DDD escapes; \\. literal escape). 22 unit tests cover root-only, single label, multiple labels, dot/backslash escapes, octal escapes, compression-pointer rejection, label-over-63 rejection, output-too-small, empty-middle-label rejection, escape-related malformed input, plus 2 round-trip property tests proving ntop(pton(text)) == text for both simple names and escaped names."}
 {"id": "bd-nsn-2", "title": "PORT: ns_name sub-bead 2 \u2014 rewire abi shims", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-nsn-epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T09:42:59.817017Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T09:42:59.817017Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T09:42:59.817017Z", "resolution": "Removed inline ns_name_ntop (~85 lines), ns_name_pton (~110 lines), __ns_name_ntop (~84 lines), __ns_name_pton (~113 lines) \u2014 total ~392 lines \u2014 from glibc_internal_abi.rs. All 4 entry points become thin shims that materialize src/dst as byte slices and call core. Note: __ns_name_pton uses the BSD return semantic (1=fully qualified, 0=not, -1=error) which differs from the public ns_name_pton (returns byte count); the shim detects the trailing dot to compute the BSD return. 173/173 abi lib + 29/29 ns_name integration tests pass; clippy + fmt clean."}
 {"id": "bd-nsn-epic", "title": "PORT: ns_name_ntop / ns_name_pton DNS wire-format codec to core::resolv::dns", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T09:42:59.817017Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T09:42:59.817017Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T09:42:59.817017Z", "resolution": "Epic complete in 2 sub-beads. ~392 lines of inline RFC 1035 DNS wire-format codec across 4 abi entry points lifted into ~190 lines of pure-safe core::resolv::dns_name (with 22 isolation-tested cases including 2 round-trip property tests). Documented the BSD vs glibc-public return-semantic difference between __ns_name_pton (1/0/-1) and ns_name_pton (byte count) \u2014 preserved in the abi shims at the boundary."}
